{
  "texts": [
    "By the locality of the underlying CFT, a TDL L extended in the (Euclidean) time direction defines a new Hilbert space H L S 1, that generalizes the conventional twisted sector for discrete group symmetries.",
    "By the state-operator correspondence in the presence of the TDL, states in H L S 1 are mapped to L-twisted sector operators, namely operators on which L can end.",
    "For nontrivial L, by the faithfulness condition (vanishing tadpole condition in [10]), the ground states in H L S 1 necessarily have conformal weight h + h > 0, and the spin spectrum contains nontrivial information about the F-symbols involving L [10].",
    "The latter can be derived by studying how symmetries act in the L-twisted sector via configurations involving other TDLs along the spatial direction.",
    "The defect Hilbert space H L S 1 generalizes in the obvious way for multiple parallel TDLs in the temporal direction which we denote asH L 1 L 2...Ln S 1."
  ]
}